## AtlasIT Infrastructure & AI Addendum

This addendum captures infrastructure decisions that support the AtlasIT workers. It supersedes earlier legacy documentation.

---

### ☁️ Deployment Architecture (Cloudflare-First)

AtlasIT currently ships three Workers (onboarding, orchestrator, documentation) using a shared set of Cloudflare capabilities:

| Concern          | Implementation Details |
| ---------------- | ---------------------- |
| Execution        | Cloudflare Workers (Wrangler-driven deploys) |
| State            | Cloudflare KV (session data) and D1 (structured onboarding storage) |
| Secrets          | `wrangler secret` scoped per worker (API keys, gateway tokens) |
| Scheduling       | Worker CRON triggers (limited use today) |
| Observability    | Structured logs with `x-request-id` propagation (metrics in roadmap) |

Durable Objects are planned to persist orchestrator workflow state beyond a single isolate (see `docs/roadmap.md`).

---

### 🤖 Automation & AI Usage

AI support is minimal and routed through the orchestrator:

- Approval hooks can call external AI providers via tokens stored in secrets.
- `@atlasit/shared` offers deterministic AI stubs for tests and production fallbacks.
- Future enhancements (multi-provider orchestration, evidence summarisation) remain on the roadmap.

---

### 🛡️ Security & Compliance Notes

- API keys gate onboarding/orchestrator endpoints (`x-api-key` headers).
- `ops/DEPLOYMENT_SECRETS_CHECKLIST.md` tracks required secrets and rotation guidance.
- `npm run validate:env` enforces Cloudflare token preference (`CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` over legacy `CF_API_TOKEN`).
- Secret scanning (`npm run scan:secrets`) is part of pre-push checks.

